sec.p:
Identifiable data will be accessed and used only by members of the research team at The Pennine Acute Hospitals NHS Trust. The Data Manager will (periodically, but sometime after the clinical episode) assign study numbers to the cases before providing the data to the statistician and members of the management team.
The Principal Investigator, on behalf of The Pennine Acute Hospitals NHS Trust, is the custodian of the data;
Research participants have the right to revoke their authorization for the use of personal information;
Participants will not be identifiable in any future publication.
